<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_Toddlers" s="156321">
  <T n="category">10175<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_SimLife--></T>
  <T n="name">0x4104E002<!--String: "Toddler Care"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddlers_1.png" n="image">2f7d0004:00000000:70699f21bdccf8c6</T>
      <T n="text">0x3C02F58C<!--String: "Toddlers need others to provide for their Needs. A Toddler Bed, High Chair, and Potty will also greatly help to ensure your Toddler is getting the best care. Make sure to pay attention to your Toddlers’ Needs or you might find the Social Worker will whisk away your little tyke."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddlers_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:70699f21bdccf8c5</T>
      <T n="text">0x3E002C4C<!--String: "For optimal toddler happiness, you should head into Build Mode and browse the Toddler sort. Toddler Beds, High Chairs, Pottys, Tablets… everything a growing toddler needs!\n\nAll of these can be found by clicking on Objects by Room / Kids’ Room sort, and then clicking on the stack of blocks to open up the Toddlers sort."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddlers_3.png" n="image">2f7d0004:00000000:70699f21bdccf8c4</T>
      <T n="text">0xCB6E2806<!--String: "Time for bed… or maybe it’s just time for the adults to relax. You can let your little ones sleep on the floor, couch, or a chair, but your Toddler will rest better if you click on the Toddler or a Toddler Bed and choose Put to Sleep, or Read to Sleep."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddlers_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:70699f21bdccf8c3</T>
      <T n="text">0xCA58E7E6<!--String: "Toddlers can use their diaper to fulfill their Bladder need, but maybe you don’t want a little stinker running around. Get a Potty, and Potty Train your Toddler!\n\nClick on the Potty and choose Potty Train. As your Toddler gets better at using the Potty, they will be able to go on their own with confidence!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T p="InGame\UI\Tutorial\Client\LifeLessons\Toddlers_5.png" n="image">2f7d0004:00000000:70699f21bdccf8c2</T>
      <T n="text">0xC8479ABE<!--String: "Toddlers have a special relationship with some Sims; their Parents and Caregivers. Sims that fall into one of those two groups will concern themselves with and care for the Needs of the toddler.\n\nYou can also choose to become (or remove) yourself as a Caregiver by selecting the Adopt as Care Dependent interaction in the Toddler Care menu."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_Family</E>
  </L>
